Release Notes:
This release is ripped from Transformers: Energon Ultimate Collection.  The DVDs
did not contain any extras.

America's Energon has 51 episodes, while Japan's Transformers: Superlink has 52
episodes.  For unknown reason's, Superlink's episode 33, Return! Our Scorponok, was
never dubbed into English and broadcast in America.  This release acknowledges the
omission by keeping the original episode numbering, and leaving a gap at the
missing 33rd episode.

The removal of the episode leaves Energon with a couple of pronounced holes in its
ongoing story, as plots already in motion are expanded on and important events
occur which influence future episodes.  If you're interested in seeing what you've
missed, check out TV-Nihon's excellent fansub of Transformers: Superlink. <a href="
http://www.tvnihon.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.tvnihon.com/</a>


Background:
Transformers: Energon, known as Transformers: Superlink in Japan, is the animated
series which ran from 2004-2005.  It is the second co-production between Hasbro and
Takara.

Transformers: Armada, Transformers: Energon and Transformers: Cybertron, form the
continuity family known as the Unicron Trilogy. 


Plot:
It has been 10 years since the war of the Mini-Cons and the apparent destruction of
Unicron and Galvatron, and the Autobots and Decepticons, working together, have
entered into a secret alliance with humankind, building vast Cybertron Cities on
Earth and in the solar system to mine for energon, the energy-rich mineral that
Transformers need to survive.  But ten years is a long time... and in the darkness
of space, evil is beginning to rise again...
